<subSubSection box="[151,548,1626,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,548,1626,1653]" box="[151,548,1626,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,548,1626,1653]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,548,1626,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1913" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[238,548,1626,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,356,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">Tegotettix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, J. L." box="[364,548,1626,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" pagination="39 - 54" refId="ref6596" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1913) Studies of Tetriginae (Acrydinae) from Sarawak Museum, Borneo. The Sarawak Museum Journal, 1 (3), 39 - 54." type="journal article" year="1913">Hancock, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="201" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1698,2013]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="201" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,813,1698,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">Justification of the generic placement of the new species</emphasis>
. The new species is placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1913" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1264,1373,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">Tegotettix</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, J. L." pageId="2" pageNumber="200" pagination="39 - 54" refId="ref6596" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1913) Studies of Tetriginae (Acrydinae) from Sarawak Museum, Borneo. The Sarawak Museum Journal, 1 (3), 39 - 54." type="journal article" year="1913">Hancock, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with the 
<typeStatus box="[386,434,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hancock, 1913" authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[530,826,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">
<emphasis box="[530,649,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">T. armatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, J. L." box="[656,826,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" pagination="39 - 54" refId="ref6596" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1913) Studies of Tetriginae (Acrydinae) from Sarawak Museum, Borneo. The Sarawak Museum Journal, 1 (3), 39 - 54." type="journal article" year="1913">Hancock, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Borneo. 
<taxonomicName authority="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo, 2021" authorityName="Patano &amp; Mohagan &amp; Tumbrinck &amp; Amoroso &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2021" box="[991,1086,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derijei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[991,1086,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">T derijei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1094,1157,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1094,1150,1735,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gunther, 1935)" authorityName="Borneo" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[264,593,1770,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristiferus">
<emphasis box="[264,405,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">T. cristiferus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, K." box="[419,584,1770,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" pagination="257 - 263" refId="ref6482" refString="Gunther, K. (1935) Acrydiinen (Orth. Acrididae) aus dem mittleren Ostrorneo gesammelt von H. C. Siebers 1925. Arbeiten uber Morphologische und Taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlem, 2 (4), 257 - 263." type="journal article" year="1935">Günther, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[845,893,1771,1797]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">type</typeStatus>
series originating from central-east Borneo. The two species share almost all morphological traits, except for those related to the arrangement and height of the pronotal projections. Thus, the new species is placed within the genus 
<emphasis box="[906,1023,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[906,1019,1843,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tegotettix</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
At first sight, it is also similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1879,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">type</typeStatus>
species, but as they do not share the traits related to the head (e.g., the position of the bifurcation of the frontal costa), this superficial similarity could probably be a result of convergent evolution. With the newly proposed species, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[321,430,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,430,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="200">Tegotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes ten species; here, we briefly review the current taxonomy of the genus. The genus can be divided into three species groups, each of which includes species of very similar morphology. However, not a lot of characters unite the three groups within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[835,944,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[835,944,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">Tegotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and future research could result in the erection of three separate genera. The character that should unite all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[883,992,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,992,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">Tegotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are its high fastigial horns, but even to this rule, exceptions do exist, i.e., the low fastigial horns in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[907,1055,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittarius">
<emphasis box="[907,1055,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">T. sagittarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1938" box="[1109,1291,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novaeguineae">
<emphasis box="[1109,1291,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="201">T. novaeguineae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
